Registry, Started, 	ProviderName=Registry
	NewProviderState=Started

	SequenceNumber=1

	HostName=ConsoleHost
	HostVersion=5.1.19041.5007
	HostId=0f6253ea-a8fc-49cf-95f7-d5b30b2a2a46
	HostApplication=powershell.exe & {$ports = Get-content "C:\Users\ADMIN_~1\AppData\Local\Temp\file\data\src\top-128.txt"
$file = "$env:USERPROFILE\Desktop\open-ports.txt"
$totalopen = 0
$totalports = 0
New-Item $file -Force
foreach ($port in $ports) {
 $test = new-object system.Net.Sockets.TcpClient
 $wait = $test.beginConnect("allports.exposed", $port, $null, $null)
 $wait.asyncwaithandle.waitone(250, $false) | Out-Null
 $totalports++ | Out-Null
 if ($test.Connected) {
 $result = "$port open" 
 Write-Host -ForegroundColor Green $result
 $result | Out-File -Encoding ASCII -append $file
 $totalopen++ | Out-Null
 }
 else {
 $result = "$port closed" 
 Write-Host -ForegroundColor Red $result
 $totalclosed++ | Out-Null
 $result | Out-File -Encoding ASCII -append $file
 }
}
$results = "There were a total of $totalopen open ports out of $totalports ports tested."
$results | Out-File -Encoding ASCII -append $file
Write-Host $results}
	EngineVersion=
	RunspaceId=
	PipelineId=
	CommandName=
	CommandType=
	ScriptName=
	CommandPath=
	CommandLine=
